README

This project contains the data and statistical analyses used by the
MLAO to study the School District of Mt. Lebanon, Pennsylvania.  For
more information about the MLAO, see

    http://www.mlao.org/


REQUIREMENTS

To run the analyses in this project, you will need a Unix-like
operating system (e.g., Linux or Mac OS X) and the following software:

* The R statistical computing system
  http://www.r-project.org/

* The ggplot2 package for R
  http://had.co.nz/ggplot2/

* GNU Make (probably already installed on your computer)
  http://www.gnu.org/software/make/


RUNNING THE ANALYSES

Enter "make" at the command prompt.  The analyses should run,
producing results on standard output and statistical graphs saved to
the file system in PDF and PNG files.


QUESTIONS

If you have any questions about these data or analyses, please
direct them to Tom Moertel <tom@mlao.org>.
